The paper deals with the problem of computing all-pairs shortest paths, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The paper also mentions the use of graph parameters such as clique-width and modular-width, which are commonly studied in the sub-fields of data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational geometry (cs.CG), computational complexity (cs.CC), and graph theory (cs.GT).
